  11. DFT- DimCrimeStatus

Using SSIS Toolbox, the following components will be drag in the Control Flow Dashboard:

Drag and drop the Data Flow - right click Rename it as DFT- DimCrimeStatus.

Double click the Data Flow Task –

·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Source – Double click and add the Source connection manager and Data access mode select SQL Command – Copy the below code and paste in the SQL command text box.  And select OK.

select 
  [ UCR Code], 
  [UCR Offense Description], 
  [NIBRS Code], 
  [Offense Status], 
  case when [UCR Offense Description] in (
    'AGGRAVATED ASSAULT', 'ANIMAL CRUELTY', 
    'ARSON', 'ASSAULT', 'AUTO THEFT - UUMV', 
    'BRIBERY', 'BURGLARY', 'CHILD (OFFENSES AGAINST)', 
    'EMBEZZLEMENT', 'FORGERY &  COUNTERFEIT', 
    'FORGERY & COUNTERFEITING', 'FRAUD', 
    'GAMBLING', 'HUMAN TRAFFICKING', 
    'KIDNAPPING/ABDUCTION', 'MOTOR VEHICLE THEFT', 
    'MURDER', 'NARCOTICS/DRUGS', 'PORNOGRAPHY/OBSCENE MATERIAL', 
    'PROSTITUTION', 'ROBBERY', 'THEFT'
  ) then 'Violent Crimes' when [UCR Offense Description] in (
    'CRIMINAL MISCHIEF/VANDALISM', 'DISORDERLY
CONDUCT', 
    'DRUNK &
DISORDERLY', 'DWI', 'FAIL TO ID', 
    'FAMILY OFFENSES NONVIOLENT', 'INTOXICATION
MANSLAUGHTER', 
    'LIQUOR', 'WEAPONS'
  ) then 'Major Crimes' when [UCR Offense Description] in (
    'ACCIDENTAL INJURY', 'ANIMAL BITE', 
    'ATTEMPTED SUICIDE', 'FIREARMS ACCIDENT', 
    'FOUND PROPERTY', 'HOME ACCIDENT', 
    'LOST PROPERTY', 'MOTOR VEHICLE ACCIDENT', 
    'NO UCR
REPORTABLE OFFENSE', 'OCCUPATIONAL ACCIDENT', 
    'OTHER OFFENSES', 'SUDDEN DEATH', 
    'TRAFFIC', 'TRAFFIC
FATALITY'
  ) then 'Minor Crimes' else NULL End [CrimeStatus] 
from 
  DallasCrimeData_Staging..DallasCrimeStaging 
where 
  [ UCR Code] is not null 
  and [NIBRS Group] is not null 
group by 
  [ UCR Code], 
  [UCR Offense Description], 
  [NIBRS Group], 
  [NIBRS Code], 
  [Offense Status] 
order by 
  [ UCR Code]

·         Drag and drop the derived column - use the Derived column Code and add the as shown in the Gif – Use the code below fig for creating the columns 


·         Drag and drop Lookup and configure as follows

1.     General tab – Specify how to handle rows with no matching entries – select Redirect rows to no match output.

2.     Connection tab – OLE DB Connection manger – Select the destination connection manager and Use a table or a view – select DimCrimeStatus from the dropdown.

3.     Columns tab – make connection Source to destination as shown in fig and select OK                                                       


·         Make a Copy of the Lookup and then connect the First lookup to the copied lookup – select the option shown below-


·         Double click the 2nd lookup to go the Column Tab – unselect the Crimekey and Match the Column from the source’s column to that in destination’s columns as shown in fig.


·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Command and make connection from the 2nd lookup to it – make connection as shown below fig.



·         Double click the OLE DB command to configure it

1.     Connection Manager Tab – connect to the destination connection manager

2.     Component Properties Tab – in the SQL command – copy and paste the below code   and select OK

U      update   DimCrimeStatus 
set 
  [UCRCode] = ?, 
  [UCROffenseDescription] = ?, 
  [NIBRSCode] = ?, 
  [OffenseStatus] = ?, 
  [CrimeStatus] = ?, 
  [RecordFlag] = 1, 
  [Effectivedate] = getdate(), 
  [EndDate] = getdate()-1 
where 
  [CrimeKey] = ?

Select  distinct  [Weapon Used]
